<% require_stylesheet 'omega_services.css' %>
<h1 class="page-content corners-top">
 Welcome to Add a Service Wizard
</h1>
<div class="page-content corners-bottom">



<p>
 <span class="first-l">T</span>he Add a Service Wizard allows you to add a service from a list
  of sample services in the library. This page introduces you to the
  steps involved in this process.
</p>
<p>
  <span class="first-l">W</span>hat do I do next?
  When you are ready to continue, press the Next button to continue on to
  the Select Service Type Page. If you would like to exit the Wizard without
  creating a new Service, press the Cancel button.
</p>
<p>
<span class="first-l">H</span>ow did I get here?
  The Add a Service Wizard: Introduction Page appears when you select
  to add a service using a Wizard. The panel on the right gives an overview of each step in the process.  
</p>


  <%= om_button(:icon=>'next') do %>
      <%= button_to 'Next', service_wizard_services_url(:step => '1') %>
  <% end %>
</div>

<% content_for :sidebar do %>
    <%= render :partial => "layouts/sidebar_services_introduction" %>
<% end %>